    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.202634>
    dc:description "FIGURES 42 – 48. Myrsidea cicchinoi: (42) metathorax and dorsoventral abdomen of female; (43) metathorax and dorsoventral abdomen of male; (44) male genital sac sclerite. Myrsidea cinnamomei: (45) male genital sac sclerite. Myrsidea castroae n. sp.: (46) metathorax and dorsoventral abdomen of female; (47) metathorax and dorsoventral abdomen of male; (48) male genital sac sclerite." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/202634/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.202635>
    dc:description "FIGURE 49. Phylogeny based on maximum likelihood analysis of 379 bp of the mitochondrial COI gene for Myrsidea species analyzed by Price and Johnson (2009) and additional species described or redescribed in this paper (bold names). Search involved 10 random addition replicates with the GTR + I + G model following Price and Johnson (2009)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/202635/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

